<item>
            <title>[PIG-2767] Pig creates wrong schema after dereferencing nested tuple fields</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-2767</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The following script fails:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;data = LOAD &apos;test_data.txt&apos; USING PigStorage() AS (f1: int, f2: int, f3:&lt;br/&gt;
int, f4: int);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;nested = FOREACH data GENERATE f1, (f2, f3, f4) AS nested_tuple;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;dereferenced = FOREACH nested GENERATE f1, nested_tuple.(f2, f3);&lt;br/&gt;
DESCRIBE dereferenced;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;uses_dereferenced = FOREACH dereferenced GENERATE nested_tuple.f3;&lt;br/&gt;
DESCRIBE uses_dereferenced;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The schema of &quot;dereferenced&quot; should be &lt;/p&gt;
{f1: int, nested_tuple: (f2: int,
f3: int)}
&lt;p&gt;. DESCRIBE thinks it is &lt;/p&gt;
{f1: int, f2: int}
&lt;p&gt; instead. When dump is&lt;br/&gt;
used, the data is actually in form of the correct schema however, ex.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(1,(2,3))&lt;br/&gt;
(5,(6,7))&lt;br/&gt;
...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is not just a problem with DESCRIBE. Because the schema is incorrect,&lt;br/&gt;
the reference to &quot;nested_tuple&quot; in the &quot;uses_dereferenced&quot; statement is&lt;br/&gt;
considered to be invalid, and the script fails to run. The error is:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Invalid field projection. Projected field &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;nested_tuple&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; does not exist in&lt;br/&gt;
schema: f1:int,f2:int.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Amazon EMR, patched to use Pig 0.10.0&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
