                            <comment id="13400923" author="onetangentburn" created="Mon, 25 Jun 2012 22:33:31 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;The &apos;text_data.txt&apos; used in the script.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13500604" author="julienledem" created="Mon, 19 Nov 2012 20:12:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This will be fixed in a future release&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13633111" author="alangates" created="Tue, 16 Apr 2013 19:09:17 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;+1.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13637368" author="prkommireddi" created="Sat, 20 Apr 2013 22:24:06 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;With Alan&apos;s +1, this can be committed?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13637385" author="cheolsoo" created="Sat, 20 Apr 2013 23:10:56 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Wait. I think there is a case that is not covered by the patch. What if we have multiple levels of nesting?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Consider the following example:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
a = load &apos;a&apos; as (field1: &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;, field2: &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;, field3: &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; );
b = foreach a generate field1, TOTUPLE(TOTUPLE(field2, field3));
c = foreach a generate field1, ((field2, field3));
describe b;
describe c;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With the patch, this still gives me incorrect results:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
b: {field1: &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;,org.apache.pig.builtin.totuple_org.apache.pig.builtin.totuple_field3_13_14: (org.apache.pig.builtin.totuple_field3_13: (field2: &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;,field3: &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;))}
c: {field1: &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;,org.apache.pig.builtin.totuple_field3_23: (field2: &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;,field3: &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;)}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13638228" author="daijy" created="Mon, 22 Apr 2013 18:57:29 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=cheolsoo&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;cheolsoo&quot;&gt;Cheolsoo Park&lt;/a&gt;, thanks for testing more. I believe that&apos;s a different issue. In &quot;((field2, field3))&quot;, the inner parentheses translate to TOTUPLE, and the outer one does not. There is ambiguity in the grammar. I remember there is a discussion, we agree that we translate parentheses into TOTUPLE only when there are more than 1 items inside. This is equivalent to the python style.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13638351" author="cheolsoo" created="Mon, 22 Apr 2013 20:20:56 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=daijy&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;daijy&quot;&gt;Daniel Dai&lt;/a&gt;, thank you very much for the clarification. That case, I have no objection.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13638391" author="daijy" created="Mon, 22 Apr 2013 21:13:20 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch committed to trunk.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
